Cache ,Cookies
Cache: 	Cache is employed to store the web site content for the long run purpose.
Cache’s website contents are stored in browser only.
It expires manually.
It consumes large space in terms of capacity.
Cache stores the contents like html pages, images, Javascript, CSS etc.
Cache does not send the response with requests.

Cookies:
While cookie is employed to store user choices.
While cookie’s contents are stored in both server and browser.
While it expires automatically.
While it consumes less space in terms of capacity.
While the types of cookies are: Transient and persistent cookies
While cookie sends the response with requests.
